Hungary Banks to Get Tax Break for SME Loans, Napi Gazdasag Says

-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 
2011-05-13T07:06:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-13/hungary-banks-to-get-tax-break-for-sme-loans-napi-gazdasag-says.html
Hungarian lenders may be able to use
fresh loans to small and medium-sized enterprises to reduce
their bank-tax liability by as much as 15 percent,  Napi Gazdasag 
reported today.  The business newspaper cited a government proposal on bank
lending policy which it said is “ready to be signed.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest 
 agergely@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Kirkland in  London  at 
 skirkland@bloomberg.net . 